  "stimulus_html": "<p>Hydrocarbon <b>A</b>, C<sub>10</sub>H<sub>14</sub>, has a UV absorption at <i>λ</i><sub>max</sub> = 236 nm and gives hydrocarbon <b>B</b>, C<sub>10</sub>H<sub>18</sub>, on hydrogenation. Ozonolysis of <b>A</b>, followed by zinc/acetic acid treatment, yields the following diketo dialdehyde:</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down-30\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBZ2dWIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--d06fc89dc6534a95fd6ea38c83457995c86d18d2/OChem_14_EC_032.jpg\" alt=\"The condensed formula of compound has a 10-carbon chain. C 1, C 5, C 6, and C 10 are all double-bonded to oxygen atoms.\">\n<p>An illustration shows the structure of diketo dialdehyde. It shows two carbonyl groups single bonded to each other. Each carbonyl group is bonded to a chain of three methylene groups and then to an aldehyde group.</p>",
